text: Ypsolopha contractella is a moth of the family Ypsolophidae. It is known from Japan (the islands of Hokkaido and Honshu), Korea, north-eastern China and the Russian Far East. The length of the forewings is 7.3-11.2 mm. ==References== Category:Ypsolophidae Category:Moths of Asia Category:Taxa named by Aristide Caradja
title: Ypsolopha contractella
